Text.Value: Who are you?
It's for her sister's wedding. Miri had it when she ran out.
Maybe. What do you want me to ask?
I already know where it is.
Where is your sister's dowry?
I've done enough for you.
*The corpse regards you lifelessly.*
*The spell's power wanes. You can ask no more questions.*
*The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*
Please.
I trust you to get it for me. I can't leave her.
You can stop now. Let her rest.
... finding... husband... Benryn... inside...
She had her sister's dowry. I'd hoped she could tell us where it is.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sighs before the line. He's resigned, explaining something he knows doesn't matter.

Text.Value: Please, leave her be. She deserves peace.
Oh. It was probably pointless anyway.
She didn't make it far. It'll be close.
Where is Benryn?
I said no.
... dowry... for sister... in barn...
The barn? She must mean one of the empty buildings behind the inn.
I already found it. Here, take it. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Ask his question.
Be quiet. I have questions of my own.
The dowry. She'd know where it is.

EditorData.NodeContext: Having an 'aha' moment (but not excited - he's still grieving)

Text.Value: I'll look around. Any idea where it's stashed?
How did you die?
... inside... room... top floor...
You... what?
Leave.
What's wrong with you? Let her go!

EditorData.NodeContext: Benryn feels like the player is desecrating his wife's corpse.

Text.Value: I know this doesn't change anything, but it helps. Thank you.
Heartless bastard... let her go!
Stop worrying about the dowry. It's gone.
Let her go. And go to hell.
Did you have any valuables nearby?
I can't. She won't answer any more questions.
You're a medium! You're going to speak to her.
No, you're right. Those monsters could've taken it.
Could you ask her something for me?
Why were you at the inn?
I'd hoped she could tell us where she took the dowry.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sighs before the line. He's resigned, explaining something he knows doesn't matter.

Text.Value: ... door... locked... trapped... fire...
This dowry? I'm keeping it as payment for saving your life.
Leave.
Fine. I hope you choke on it.
... Mirileth... farmer...
... from Elturgard... travelling... sister's wedding...

Synopsis: The Cult of the Absolute has ransacked the inn at Waukeen's Rest and kidnapped Duke Stelmane of Baldur's Gate. The player arrives after the carnage, finding corpses strewn about. The player casts 'Speak with Dead' on one of these corpses - a civilian that was caught in the middle. She stopped in Wakeen's Rest with her husband and daughter in the middle of their journey to Waterdeep for a wedding. She watched her family butchered by goblins before being killed herself.
